description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an approachable, professional, flexible and experienced person to provide booking and administrative support. The successful applicant will work in the Therapy Department, Royal Cornwall Hospital. The post holder will work as part of a Therapy wide departmental administrative team to provide cover, assistance and support with out-patient and in-patient caseloads plus other related duties and may on occasion need to work at other sites.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be the first point of contact for patient enquiries plus direct appointment booking which involves negotiating appointment dates and times. Other related duties include processing letters eg clinic letters and documents, use of the PAS system, recording telephone messages appropriately and ensuring that attendances and outcomes from clinic appointments are accurately recorded and patients are informed of future appointments. Other duties include maintaining stationery supplies, ordering stock and equipment, locating and copying paperwork for medico-legal purposes plus meeting related duties with producing agendas and taking minutes. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Marie Oliver- Clinical Admin Lead, 01872 253738 or marie.oliver4@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
